on of the American welfare state. Since the 1970s, and the devastating blow dealt to Cold War ideology by America's defeat in Vietnam, Americans have returned to their characteristic distrust of government. With the collapse of the Soviet Union in 1991, Brands contends, the fate of American liberalism was sealed-and we continue to live with the consequences of its demise.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aCulture politiquexHistoirex20e sièclexÉtats-Unis. 0aLiberalismxHistoryx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aLiberalismzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aLibéralismexHistoirex20e sièclexÉtats-Unis. 0aPolitical culturexHistoryx20th centuryxUnited States. 0aPolitical culturezUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300127744423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300127744.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles